The Economic and Financial Crimes Commission (EFCC) has revealed why the former Zamfara Governor Abdulaziz Yari was arrested by their operatives. According to the News Agency of Nigeria (NAN), an authoritative source in the EFCC disclosed that Yari was arrested over alleged involvement in the N84 billion fraud allegation against the former Accountant General of the Federation (AGF) Ahmed Idris. According to NAN, the source further stated that the Chairman and Managing Director of Finex Professional, Mr Anthony Yaro was also arrested alongside the former Governor on Sunday. -Advertisement- The source said that Yari allegedly benefited to the tune of N22 billion through Finex Professional and the amount was paid to one Akindele by the former AGF from the N84 billion through Finex Professional. Recall that the former AGF was arrested on May 16 over alleged diversion and laundering of N84 billion.